Typedef Documentation

typedef void(* CAN_ErrStatusAppCallBack) (CAN_Handle handle, CAN_ErrStatusResp *errStatusResp)

Application specified callback function which is invoked by the CAN driver on error or status change.

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the CAN Driver
[out]errStatusRespResponse structure populated with the value of the fields that caused the error or status interrupt.
Return values
Notapplicable
typedef void(* CAN_MsgObjAppCallBack) (CAN_MsgObjHandle handle, uint32_t msgObjectNum, CAN_Direction direction)

Application specified callback function which is invoked by the CAN driver once transmit is complete or data has been received for the specified message object.

Parameters
[in]handleMessage object handle for which the callback function is invoked.
[in]msgObjectNumMessage Object number for which the callback is invoked.
[in]directionIndicates transmit or receive
Return values
Notapplicable

Enumeration Type Documentation

enum CAN_DCANMode_t

This enumeration defines the values used to represent the DCAN mode of operation.

Enumerator
CAN_DCANMode_NORMAL 

DCAN normal operational mode

CAN_DCANMode_INIT 

DCAN initialization mode

enum CAN_DCANTestMode_t

This enumeration defines DCAN test modes.

Enumerator
CAN_DCANTestMode_NONE 

All DCAN test mode is disabled. Use for normal operation.

CAN_DCANTestMode_SILENT 

DCAN Silent test mode

CAN_DCANTestMode_LPBACK 

DCAN loopback test mode

CAN_DCANTestMode_LPBACK_SILENT 

DCAN loopback with silent test mode

CAN_DCANTestMode_EXT_LPBACK 

DCAN external loopback test mode

enum CAN_DCANXidType_t

This enumeration defines the values used to represent the DCAN Identifier Type.

Enumerator
CAN_DCANXidType_11_BIT 

11bit DCAN Identifier

CAN_DCANXidType_29_BIT 

29bit DCAN Identifier

enum CAN_Direction_t

This enumeration defines the values used to set the direction of message object.

Enumerator
CAN_Direction_RX 

Message object used to receive data

CAN_Direction_TX 

Message object used to transmit data

enum CAN_Option_t

This enumeration defines the values used to represent the GET/SET options.

See also
CAN_OptionTLV
Enumerator
CAN_Option_DCAN_ERROR_COUNTER 

Used to get the DCAN Tx and Rx error counters

See also
CAN_getOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be sizeof(CAN_DCANErrorCounter) for this option.

CAN_Option_DCAN_PARITY_ERROR 

Used to get the DCAN parity error information

See also
CAN_getOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be sizeof(CAN_DCANParityError) for this option.

CAN_Option_DCAN_MSG_OBJECT_STATS 

Used to get the DCAN message object software maintained statistics

See also
CAN_getOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be sizeof(CAN_DCANMsgObjectStats) for this option. Application must fill in the message object handle for which the statistics is requested.

CAN_Option_DCAN_ECC_ERROR_STATUS 

Used to get the DCAN ECC error status

See also
CAN_getOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be sizeof(CAN_DCANEccErrSts) for this option.

CAN_Option_DCAN_ECC_DIAG_ERROR_STATUS 

Used to get the DCAN ECC Diagnostics error status

See also
CAN_getOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be sizeof(CAN_DCANEccErrSts) for this option.

CAN_Option_DCAN_MODE 

Used to put the DCAN module in init or operational state

See also
CAN_setOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be 1 byte for this option. Valid values: Refer to (CAN_DCANMode)

CAN_Option_DCAN_PARITY 

Used to enable or disable parity

See also
CAN_setOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be 1 byte for this option. Valid values are 1 - Parity is enabled 0 - Parity is disabled

CAN_Option_DCAN_ECC_DIAG 

Used to enable or disable ECC Diagnostics

See also
CAN_setOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be 1 byte for this option. Valid values are 1 - ECC Diagnostics is enabled 0 - ECC Diagnostics is disabled

CAN_Option_DCAN_CLEAR_ECC_ERROR_STATUS 

Used to clear the DCAN ECC error status

See also
CAN_setOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be 1 byte for this option. Valid values is 1.

CAN_Option_DCAN_CLEAR_ECC_DIAG_ERROR_STATUS 

Used to clear the DCAN ECC Diagnostics error status

See also
CAN_setOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be 1 byte for this option. Valid values is 1.

CAN_Option_DCAN_POWER_DOWN 

Used to request a local power down or wakeup from a local power down

See also
CAN_setOptions

NOTE: The length in the TLV should be 1 byte for this option. Valid values are 1 - DCAN Sleep 0 - DCAN Wakeup
